REST verbs + corresponding response HTTP status codes

https://httpstatuses.com/
HTTP statuses 200-299 = success
HTTP statuses 300-399 = info / moved
HTTP statuses 400-499 = missing / other errors
    - most commonly you'll see 400, 401, 403, 404
HTTP statuses 500-599 = server errors
    - most commonly you'll see 500, 502, 503

GET /items
    - send no body, returns all items (or paginated list of items)
    - returns 200 ok or 404 not found
GET /items/<id>
    - send no body, returns item with id
    - returns 200 ok or 404 not found
POST /items
    - include a json body, creates a new item
    - returns 201 (created), 204 (no content)
PATCH /items/<id>
    - send partial updates, updates those specific fields on item
    - returns 200 or 202
PUT /items/<id>
    - send a full item in json body, replaces the entire item
    - less used than PATCH
    - returns 200 or 202
DELETE /items/<id>
    - deletes item with id
    - returns 200